ass="nav-link" href="/~glxing/funding/">Funding</a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/~glxing/service/">Service</a> </li> <li class="nav-item"> <a class="nav-link" href="https://aiot.ie.cuhk.edu.hk" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank"> Team </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </nav> <progress id="progress" value="0"> <div class="progress-container"> <span class="progress-bar"></span> </div> </progress> </header> <div class="container mt-5"> <div class="post"> <header class="post-header"> <div> </div> <h1 class="post-title"> <span class="font-weight-bold">Guoliang</span> <div class="profile float-right"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 480px)" srcset="/~glxing/assets/img/guoliang-xing-480.webp"></source> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 800px)" srcset="/~glxing/assets/img/guoliang-xing-800.webp"></source> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="/~glxing/assets/img/guoliang-xing-1400.webp"></source> <img src="/~glxing/assets/img/guoliang-xing.jpg" class="img-fluid z-depth-1 rounded" width="auto" height="auto" alt="guoliang-xing.jpg" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"> </picture> </figure> </div> Xing </h1> <p class="desc">Professor, ACM Fellow, IEEE Fellow<br> <a href="https://www.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Department of Information Engineering</a><br><a href="https://www.cse.cuhk.edu.hk/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Department of Computer Science and Engineering (Courtesy)</a><br>Director, <a href="https://aiot.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">CUHK AIoT Lab</a><br><a href="https://cuhk.edu.hk/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">The Chinese University of Hong Kong</a><br>Email: glxing [@] ie.cuhk.edu.hk<br>Rm 736, Ho Sin Hang Engineering Building,<br>CUHK, Shatin, NT, Hong Kong SAR</p> <br><br> </header> <article> <div class="clearfix"> <p>Prof. Guoliang Xing received his B.S. and M.S. degrees from Xi’an Jiao Tong University, China, in 1998 and 2001, respectively, and his D.Sc. degree from Washington University in St. Louis in 2006. He is currently a Professor in the Department of Information Engineering at The Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK). Previously, he served as a faculty member at the City University of Hong Kong and Michigan State University, USA.</p> <p>Prof. Xing’s research lies at the intersection of systems and Embedded AI, with transformative applications in healthcare, autonomous driving, and sustainability. His research group is at the forefront of advancements in Internet of Things (IoT), Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS), embedded sensor systems, and wireless networks. Highlights of his work include leading the development and field deployment of large-scale systems for roadside infrastructure-assisted autonomous driving, early clinical diagnosis and treatment of Alzheimer’s disease, and real-time volcano monitoring. Several technologies developed in his lab have been successfully adopted by industry and have received significant recognition from leading global companies.</p> <p>Prof. Xing has received several prestigious awards, including the US NSF CAREER Award (2010), the Withrow Rising Scholar Award from Michigan State University (2014), Research Excellence Award, and the Outstanding Fellow from CUHK (2024). His work has received 6 Best Paper Awards, 5 Best Demo/Poster/Artifact Awards, and 7 Best Paper Finalist distinctions at top-tier international conferences such as MobiCom, MobiSys, SenSys, ICNP, and IPSN. He is a Fellow of both the ACM and IEEE.</p> <p>For more information about his research, visit the <a href="https://aiot.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">AIoT Lab homepage</a>. Motivated students and researchers are encouraged to explore current openings and and <a href="https://aiot.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/openings.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">join the team</a>.</p> </div> <br> <h2>News</h2> <div class="news"> <style>@media(max-width:768px){.table-responsive{max-height:45vh!important}}@media(min-width:769px){.table-responsive{max-height:60vh!important}}</style> <div class="table-responsive" style="max-height: 60vh"> <table class="table table-sm table-borderless"> <tr> <th scope="row">Sep 9,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Named Hong Kong RGC Senior Research Fellow 2025 (10 awardees across all disciplines), read the news release <a href="https://www.focus.cuhk.edu.hk/en/20250909/seven-cuhk-scholars-named-rgc-senior-research-fellows-or-research-fellows/069-staff-en/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">here</a>. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Sep 7,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Three papers of our lab have been accepted by <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobicom/2025/accepted.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiCom 2025!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 25,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “SCX: Stateless KV-Cache Encoding for Cloud-Scale Confidential Transformer Serving” was accepted by <a href="https://conferences.sigcomm.org/sigcomm/2025/program/papers-info/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SIGCOMM 2025!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">May 12,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Congratulations to <a href="https://raphaelduan.github.io/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Di</a> for receiving the <strong>Best Paper Honorable Mention Award</strong> at <a href="https://sensys.acm.org/2025/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SenSys 2025</a>! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Apr 13,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our research projects, <strong>An Intelligent LiDAR with Adaptive Focus</strong> and <strong>Sonar-based Underwater Human Activity Monitoring System</strong>, received two <strong>gold medals</strong> at the <a href="https://inventions-geneva.ch/en/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">50th International Exhibition of Inventions Geneva</a>. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jan 23,<br>2025</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Elected as an ACM Fellow, read the news release <a href="https://www.acm.org/media-center/2025/january/fellows-2024" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">here</a>. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Dec 26,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Congratulations to <strong>Zhihe</strong> for being selected for <a href="https://www.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/ie-phd-zhihe-zhao-has-been-selected-for-the-forbes-china-30-under-30/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Forbes China’s ‘30 under 30’</a> list! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Nov 27,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> At MobiCom’24, Jiahe &amp; Yuze’s work “αLiDAR: An Adaptive High-Resolution Panoramic LiDAR System” received <strong>Best Artifact Award</strong> and <strong>Best Demo Award Runner-up</strong>. The work “Soar: Design and Deployment of A Smart Roadside Infrastructure System for Autonomous Driving” co-led by Shuyao, Neiwen, Zhehao, and Xuan received <strong>Best Artifact Award Runner-up</strong>! Congratulations! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Nov 18,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Service]</strong> Serving as the Interim Joint Steering Committee Co-Chair of SenSys, IPSN, and IoTDI, and General Co-Chair of <a href="https://sensys.acm.org/2025/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SenSys’25.</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Nov 15,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Congratulations to <a href="https://zhiyuancu.github.io/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Zhiyuan</a> for receiving the Outstanding PhD Thesis Award! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Nov 15,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Received the <a href="https://www.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/prof-guoliang-xing-receives-the-research-excellence-award-2023-24/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Research Excellence Award</a>, <a href="https://www.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/prof-guoliang-xing-named-outstanding-fellow-of-the-faculty-of-engineering-2024-2029/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Outstanding Fellow </a>from Faculty of Engineering. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Nov 7,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our demo “Myotrainer: Muscle-Aware Motion Analysis and Feedback” received the <strong>Best Demo Runner-up Award</strong> at <a href="https://sensys.acm.org/2024/demos/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SenSys 2024!</a> Congrats to Yuting, Xinyan, Mu, and Di! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 14,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Funding]</strong> Received a new STG grant of HKD $39.17M as PI, titled “Foundation Models-Empowered Ambient Intelligence Systems for Early Diagnosis, Personalised Intervention, and Complex Cross-Disease Interplay Analysis of Aging-Related Degenerative Diseases”. Read the <a href="https://www.cpr.cuhk.edu.hk/en/press/cuhk-receives-over-hk54-million-from-the-rgc-for-three-funded-projects-in-strategic-topics-grant/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">press release</a> here. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jun 5,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our demo “MuRa: A Scalable Mobile Ultra-wideband Testbed for Multi-node Ranging” received the <strong>Best Demo Award</strong> at <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobisys/2024/accepted-demos.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiSys 2024!</a> Congrats to Shaoyang! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">May 15,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our demo “AD-CLIP: Privacy-Preserving, Low-Cost Synthetic Human Action Dataset for Alzheimer’s Patients via CLIP-based Models” received the <strong>Best Demo Award</strong> at <a href="https://ipsn.acm.org/2024/awards.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">IPSN 2024!</a> Congrats to Heming! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">May 15,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our paper “ArtFL: Exploiting Data Resolution in Federated Learning for Dynamic Runtime Inference via Multi-Scale Training” received the <strong>Best Paper Award</strong> at <a href="https://ipsn.acm.org/2024/awards.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">IPSN 2024!</a> Congrats to Siyang and our alum Xian! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Apr 29,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Event]</strong> Congratulations to <a href="https://xmouyang.github.io/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Xiaomin</a> who will be joing CSE@HKUST as a tenure-track Assistant Professor in Fall 2024! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Apr 20,<br>2024</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our research projects, <strong>VI-Map</strong>, <strong>Mozart</strong>, and <strong>VibVoice</strong> have won gold, silver, and bronze prizes at the <a href="https://inventions-geneva.ch/en/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">49th International Exhibition of Inventions Geneva</a>, respectively. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Oct 27,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Unleash the Potential of Image Branch for Cross-modal 3D Object Detection” was accepted by <a href="https://nips.cc/virtual/2023/index.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">NeurIPS 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Oct 23,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Wave-for-Safe: Multisensor-based Mutual Authentication for Unmanned Delivery Vehicle Services” was accepted by <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobihoc/2023/program.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiHoc 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Oct 2,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our paper “VI-Map: Infrastructure-Assisted Real-Time HD Mapping for Autonomous Driving” received <strong>Best Community Contribution Award</strong> at <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobicom/2023/program.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiCom 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Sep 20,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Miriam: Exploiting Elastic Kernels for Real-time Multi-DNN Inference on Edge GPU” was accepted by <a href="http://sensys.acm.org/2023/program/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SenSys 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Sep 20,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “EdgeFM: Leveraging Foundation Model for Open-set Learning on the Edge” was accepted by <a href="http://sensys.acm.org/2023/program/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SenSys 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Sep 9,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Timely Fusion of Surround Radar/Lidar for Object Detection in Autonomous Driving Systems” was accepted by <a href="https://date23.date-conference.com/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">DATE 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 31,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Event]</strong> Co-Chairing <a href="https://cps-iot-week2024.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">CPS-IoT Week 2024</a> in Hong Kong! Please consider to submit papers. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 30,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Event]</strong> Gave a keynote at <a href="https://www.acmturc.com/2023/en/index.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">ACM TURC (SigBed Symposium)</a>, and attended two panels. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 25,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Enabling Ubiquitous WiFi Sensing with Beamforming Reports” was accepted by <a href="https://conferences.sigcomm.org/sigcomm/2023/list-accepted.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">SIGCOMM 2023!</a> Congrats to Chenhao and Xuan! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 20,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Service]</strong> Serving on PC of MobiCom and SenSys 2024. </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jul 19,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Service]</strong> The <a href="https://aiot.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/asi" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Croucher ASI-AIoT Workshop</a> just concluded. We had six distinguished lectures, four panels, and a dozen of invited talks! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Jun 22,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Honor]</strong> Our paper “Mozart: A Mobile ToF System for Sensing in the Dark through Phase Manipulation” received the <strong>Best Paper Award</strong> at <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobisys/2023/program.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiSys 2023!</a> Congrats to Zhiyuan and Xiaomin! </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Feb 27,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Mozart: A Mobile ToF System for Sensing in the Dark through Phase Manipulation” was accepted by <a href="https://www.sigmobile.org/mobisys/2023/accepted-papers.html" style="font-weight: 500;" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">MobiSys 2023!</a> </td> </tr> <tr> <th scope="row">Feb 27,<br>2023</th> <td> <strong>[Paper]</strong> Our paper “Harmony: Heteroge